@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(DOM-ARCH-DIFF, 0029)
' @id(DOM-ARCH-DIFF)
' @desc(DOM-ARCH-DIFF, "Implemented in crates/mdd-core/src/architecture.rs: ArchDiff partitions changes by entity + id (added/removed/changed components, decisions, constraints) via the pure diff(base, head); ArchViolation + ViolationKind report broken OCL-ARCH-* invariants via the pure check(spec, model_ids). Both are pure (no IO/git), so they unit-test directly; check() backs `mdd arch status` and the validate WARNING rules.")
' Current-side domain for the architecture diff + check model (cycle 0029).
title Architecture diff + check model (current)

class ArchDiff {
  + addedComponents : List<Id>
  + removedComponents : List<Id>
  + changedComponents : List<Id>
  + addedDecisions : List<Id>
  + removedDecisions : List<Id>
  + changedDecisions : List<Id>
  + addedConstraints : List<Id>
  + removedConstraints : List<Id>
  + changedConstraints : List<Id>
  + isEmpty() : Boolean
}
class ArchViolation {
  + kind : ViolationKind
  + subject : Id
  + message : String
}
enum ViolationKind {
  DecisionMissingStatus
  SupersededMissingSuccessor
  ComponentRefUnresolved
}

ArchDiff ..> ArchitectureSpec : diff(base, head) of >
ArchViolation ..> ArchitectureSpec : check(spec, modelIds) of >
ArchViolation --> ViolationKind

note bottom of ArchViolation
  check() backs both `mdd arch status` (exits
  non-zero on any violation) and the WARNING-level
  OCL-ARCH-* rules in mdd validate:
  OCL-ARCH-DECISION-HAS-STATUS,
  OCL-ARCH-SUPERSEDE-LINKED,
  OCL-ARCH-COMPONENTS-IN-SYNC.
end note
@enduml
